              "free_text": [
                " Experiment was performed using DANCE,",
                "located on flight path 14 at the Manuel Lujan, Jr.",
                "Neutron scattering center at LANSCE."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "62-SM-147",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.9793
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Three samples of metallic",
                "samarium, enriched to 97.93% in 147 Sm, 1 cm in",
                "diameter, and weighed 1.444, 3.208, and 10.410 Mg",
                "were used."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "BAF2"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " DANCE is a 4pi array of 160 BaF2 crystals",
                "designed for studying neutron capture cross sections",
                "on small samples. DANCE was located on flight path 14,",
                "positioned 20 m from the ambient-temperature water",
                "moderator."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Incident neutron energy was determined by time",
                "of flight. Width of the proton pulses was 125 ns and",
                "flight path was 20 m."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "SPALL"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Neutrons are generated at LANSCE via",
                "spallation reactions when an 800 MeV proton beam",
                "strikes a tungsten target. The resulting neutron flux",
                "peaks near thermal energy and is approximately",
                "proportional to 1/En over the range of measurements."
              ]
            }
          ],
